OL,3,C18 year old from the Rhondda valley
OL,4,Cfears she'll be on universal credit
OL,5,Cfor life
OL,7,FAfter leaving school in January,
OL,8,FSophie was looking forward to securing
OL,9,Fher first job and gaining
OL,10,Findependence. Nine months on, and more
OL,11,Fthan 100 applications later, she is
OL,12,Fstill unemployed and uncertain about
OL,13,Fher future.
OL,15,F"I'm young, I want to do something
OL,16,Fwith my life, but I'm not. I sit on my
OL,17,Fphone every day, scrolling through the
OL,18,Fsame jobs...It's annoying," she said.
