OL,4,Cfears she'll be on universal credit
OL,5,Cfor life
OL,7,FDespite feeling grateful for the
OL,8,Ffinancial support she receives while
OL,9,Fjob searching, Sophie believes more
OL,10,Fneeds to be done to help young people
OL,11,Ffind work in areas like Rhondda Cynon
OL,12,FTaf.
OL,14,F"Universal credit is good but it's not
OL,15,Fenough...the government needs to do
OL,16,Fmore to create jobs for young people
OL,17,Fin the Rhondda, and for people in
OL,18,Fgeneral."
OL,20,F"There are so many people without jobs
OL,21,Fon Universal Credit who want to work."
