OL,4,Cfears she'll be on universal credit
OL,5,Cfor life
OL,7,FAs one of many young people who are
OL,8,Funemployed in Wales, Sophie is
OL,9,Fbeginning to question if she will ever
OL,10,Fsecure employment in her home town.
OL,12,F"It's frustrating because people tell
OL,13,Fme that there are plenty of places to
OL,14,Fwork in the Rhondda, there's not." she
OL,15,Fsaid.
OL,17,F"Sometimes I feel like I'm just not
OL,18,Fgood enough to get a job. It makes me
OL,19,Ffeel like I'll be on Universal Credit
OL,20,Ffor the rest of my life - and I don't
OL,21,Fwant to be."
